events.name: European Qualifier
events.description: England v Serbia (Kick-off 7.45pm). Mark Pougatch presents all the action from the FIFA World Cup Group K qualifier at Wembley Stadium. England produced an excellent display in September's reverse fixture to win 5-0 in Belgrade, with five different players finding the net, and they followed that up with a victory by the same scoreline in Latvia that secured their place at next year's World Cup. It remains to be seen whether Thomas Tuchel will look to experiment with his side or continue building momentum with the strongest team he has available to him, but Serbia are in need of a result as they are battling it out with Albania for second place in the group and a spot in the play-offs. With analysis from Ian Wright and Roy Keane, and commentary by Sam Matterface and Lee Dixon
